========,1,preface.
Almanor (formerly, Plumas Pines) was a census-designated place (CDP) in Plumas County, California, United States.
The population was 0 at the 2010 Census.
Almanor is located south-southeast of Chester.
========,2,History.
The name comes from three daughters of Guy C. Earl, president of the Great Western Power Co.: "Alice", "Martha", and "Elinor".
The Almanor post office opened in 1926.
========,2,Geography.
Almanor is located at (40.216857, -121.177325), on the south-west shoreline of Lake Almanor.
According to the United States Census Bureau, the CDP has a total area of , all land.
